cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.CR 

This paper presents a new type system for Typed Racket that combines occurrence typing with dependent refinement types, allowing for solver-backed reasoning about logical propositions from external theories. This work is primarily focused on programming languages and type systems (cs.PL), but also involves formal logic (cs.LO), software engineering (cs.SE), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), and cryptography and security (cs.CR) due to the use of solver-backed reasoning.
